Interface VideoDescriptor


  • public interface VideoDescriptor
    Describes a video and provides the video file location.

    • Method Detail

      • getTitle

        java.lang.String getTitle()
        Get the video title, which is provided in the feed. e.g "Push It - Salt'N Pepa - The Sims 3 Version"
        Returns:
        the video title

      • getDescription

        java.lang.String getDescription()
        Get the video description, which is provided in the feed. e.g. "Push it - The Sims 3 Version!\nSubscribe to channel\nInscreva-se!\n--Crazy Sims --"
        Returns:
        the video description

      • getAuthorName

        java.lang.String getAuthorName()
        Get the display name of the video author, which is provided in the feed. e.g "Alex M Henrique"
        Returns:
        the video author

      • getLocalUri

        java.lang.String getLocalUri()
        Get the file URI of the video. e.g. file:///storage/emulated/0/Android/data/com.incoming.push.sample/files/ Download/ooyalah5c3I3bjpcYMhc1Dr0mZhNo1SeGpMyyA.mp4
        Returns:
        the video file URI

      • getDurationMillis

        long getDurationMillis()
        Get the video duration.
        Returns:
        the duration of the video in milliseconds

      • getDurationSeconds

        int getDurationSeconds()
        Get the video duration.
        Returns:
        the duration of the video in sseconds

      • getCreatedEpoch

        long getCreatedEpoch()
        The time the video was added to the server feed.
        Returns:
        time the video was discovered in milliseconds since 1970.

      • getThumbnail

        @Nullable
android.graphics.Bitmap getThumbnail()
        Obtain a video thumbnail. This method decodes the thumbnail file synchronously so may need to be called from a background update task in cases where UI responsiveness is required.
        Returns:
        thumbnail bitmap; may be null if the file could not be found or if there was an error decoding the image.
